associate at the firm and gained experience working on personal injury cases in  colin graduated magna cum laude with a bachelor of arts degree in history from baylor university while attending law school he won numerous awards for his impressive efforts in mock trial competitions and was the winner of the  bob and karen wortham “top gun” fall practice court mock trial competition telephone  fax  cpowellhdbdlawcom  n central expy suite  dallas texas  curriculum vitae education baylor university jd  • national trial competition mock trial team • tournament of champions mock trial team • american association of justice mock trial team regional semifinalist • national criminal procedure moot court team thirdplace brief • dawson  sodd spring moot court competition semifinalistbaylor university ba history magna cum laude  bar  court admissions texasus district court for the northern district of texas honors  awards • winner of the  bob and karen wortham top gun fall practice court mock trial competition• scott douglass  mcconnico llp evidence award from baylor law american board of trial advocates award from baylor law school professional affiliations  activities • waco isd education foundation board member • heart of texas regional history fair judge  areas of practice personal injury defense product liability litigation colin powell  vyrso vyrso christian ebooks search sign in sign in with your faithlifelogos account email address password sign in forgot your password no account sign up for a free account products young adult nonfiction colin powell colin powell by gregg lewis deborah shaw lewis tweet  add to cart overview take an upclose and personal look into the lives of some wellknown christians who are successful leaders in their careers the todays heroes series features everyday people who overcame great adversity to become modernday heroes kids ages eight to twelve will be inspired by the compelling stories of courageous individuals who are making a real difference in todays heroes colin powell learn the inspiring story of how an average kid from the bronx grew up to become the first africanamerican ever appointed as secretary of state in fourth grade colin powell was put in the slow class and in high school he only got cs but when he joined the rotc while in college his life changed through hard work faith and perseverance colin powell rose through the ranks to become the first africanamerican to ever serve as the nations top military commanderchairman of the joint chiefs of staff read the compelling story of a true pioneer and an american hero in todays heroes colin powell details title colin powell author gregg lewis deborah shaw lewis genre  young adult nonfiction publisher zondervan isbn  author information gregg lewis is an award winning author or coauthor of more than fifty books including the ny times bestseller tom landry an autobiography gregg and his wife deborah have been married for more than thirtyseven years and have five adult children they currently write and live in georgia goodreads reviews reviews from goodreadscom other books in this genre  essentials for a life of significance  add to cart awesome bible heroes  add to cart awesome bible kids  add to cart awesome bible mysteries  add to cart awesome power parables  add to cart awful bible bad guys  add to cart believing in narnia a kids guide to unlocking the secret symbols of faith in cs lewis the chronicles of narnia  add to cart checklist for life for teens  days of timeless wisdom  foolproof strategies for making the most of lifes challenges and opportunities  add to cart follow us enter your email address to get vyrso updates about ebooks authors and specials submit tweet what is vyrso faq forums press room privacy contact us mobile blog copyright  faithlife  logos bible software  my american journey colin powell   christianbookcom hear about sales receive special offers  moreyou can unsubscribe at any time enter email address my account wishlist 